706752f-a.folder: Shore Boulevard & West End Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
706752f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: Shore Boulevard - West End Avenue
706752f-a.text:
Shore Boulevard, east from near West End Avenue on Sheepshead Bay, showing the old bulkhead and part of the Bay which will later be filled in when the thoroughfare will be widened. View 2 shows the new bulkhead line (left) and fill. These operations are by the W. P. A. and are part of the city's belt highway project.
View 1: March 16, 1936
View 2: June 24,1936
Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs Project

706753f-a.folder: Shore Boulevard & West End Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
706753f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: Shore Boulevard - West End Avenue
706753f-a.text:
Shore Boulevard, east from West End Avenue, along the shore of Sheepshead Bay. The views show operations being conducted by the W. P. A. in the widening of the thoroughfare. A new bulkhead line had to be constructed and part of the bay filled in to a depth of about twenty feet. On the north side of Sheepshead Bay (left) is Emmons Avenue, which is also heing widened as part of the circumferential highway system which will girt the city.
View 1: July 21, 1936
View 2: August 25, 1936
View 3: September 11, 1936
View 4: September 24, 1936
Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs "roject
